The paper deals with optimization problems related to clustering and sketching of geometric data sets, which are common topics in computer science. The use of metric measure spaces and distance functions also suggests a connection to data structures (cs.DS) and computational geometry (cs.CG). The paper also presents a general method for transforming solutions between clustering and sketching problems, which could fall under machine learning (cs.LG) or information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper discusses various notions of diameters and distances, which could relate to mathematical software (cs.MS).
